We believe that the market is heavily price in for a "rate skip" rather than a "rate pause". This is due to the recentSummary of Economic Projections (SEP)Fed Funds Rate  at 5.1% which is unchanged from the past 2 SEPs   hinting growing consensus among the committee of this "rate skip" narrative.The difference is that there is higher possibility of today's FOMC meeting outcome to see interest rate holding steady (no hike) while keeping options open for further rate hike in July FOMC.In May  we saw no SEP. Today  we should expect the SEP release. Hence  we have to look out forINCREASEorDECREASE.
